Unique if: if two are more conditions true it will shows and none of conditions true else block also abscent then also show error
1)module tb;
  initial
    begin
      int a=50;
      int b=100;
      unique if(a<=b)
        $display("a=b");
      else if(a<b)
        $display("a<b");
      else if(a>b)
        $display("a>b");
      else
        $display("exist");
    end
endmodule
# KERNEL: a=b
# ASSERT: Error: Assertion 'unique_if_1' FAILED at time: 0, testbench.sv(6), scope: tb.0unnblk. Two or more conditions are true simultaneously: a<=b (line: 6), a<b. (line: 8)
